<article class="fyre-comment-article">
  <div class="fyre-comment-wrapper">
  
  
  
  <div class="fyre-comment-user">
    <a class="fyre-comment-author"><img src="http://gravatar.com/avatar/b1d0592c3385d70d9bfab4a720b9e283/?s=50&amp;d=http://avatars.fyre.co/a/anon/50.jpg" class=
    "fyre-user-avatar" alt="Murdo Ritchie" /></a>

    <div class="fyre-comment-socialsync fyre-comment-from-livefyre"></div>
  </div>
    
  <header class="fyre-comment-head">
    <a class="fyre-comment-username">Murdo Ritchie</a> 
    
    
    <span class="fyre-comment-user-rating" style="display: none;">5pts</span>
    <span class="fyre-comment-like" style="float: right;">
      
    </span>
    
  </header>
  
  <section class="fyre-comment-body">
    <div class="fyre-comment">
      <p><p>I came across a very good three interview breakdown of both the history and current developments in the Congo, especially the role of US imperialism.


<a href="http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=33&amp;Itemid=74&amp;jumival=806" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=33&Itemid=74&jumival=806</a>

It is impossible to claim ignorance about the importance of the area nad issues after watching and listening to these interviews.</p></p>
    </div>
    
  </section>

  <footer class="fyre-comment-footer">
  </footer>
  </div>
  <div class="fyre-comment-divider"><div class="fyre-comment-divider"></div></div>

  
    
  <div class="fyre-comment-replies fyre-comment-container fyre-comment-replies-indent">
  
